Amazon RDS (Relational Database Service)


Amazon RDS is a managed database service that supports MySQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB, Oracle, and SQL Server. It automates tasks like backups, updates, and scaling.



What I Learned
Launching an RDS instance

Understanding DB engines (MySQL, PostgreSQL, etc.)

Security groups for database access

Automated backups and snapshots

How applications connect to RDS

Basic database concepts (storage, endpoints, security)



Why RDS Matters


RDS makes databases easier to manage, more reliable, and scalable without manual admin work.






